# Motivation
 
## Covariance Structures in MET Data

In multi-environment trials, we want to capture how genetic effects correlate across environments. The covariance structure you choose is a important decision on the modelling stage. Here, we want to investigate the impact of covariance structure choice on genetic parameter estimates, marginal BLUPS, and ranking correspondence.

We compare covariance structures at three levels:
(i) model fit,
(ii) implied genetic covariance, and
(iii) impact on ranking based on marginal blups.

