## Conditional BLUPs for the rr+dia1 gmodel. 

A factor analytic model (fa) of order k, and their variations (rr+diag, facv, sfa) denoted FAk, is assumed for the genetic effects or BLUPs ($\mu_g$) as:

$$ \mu_g = (\Lambda \otimes I_m) f + \delta $$

where $\Lambda$ is the p × k matrix of environment loadings for individual factors; $f$ is the mk−vector of variety scores (ordered as varieties within factors) and $\delta$ is the mp−vector of lack of fit effects.

For comparation purposes, we will define marginal BLUP as the overall genetic value of a genotype across environments, integrating out (averaging over) environments ($(\Lambda \otimes I_m) f$), and conditional BLUP as the sum of the two components: factor part + lack of fit part ($(\Lambda \otimes I_m) f + \delta$) within environment.

For the rr + diag models the 'asreml-R' output is organized as: 
- BLUP_RR (marginal BLUPs);
- Scores; and
- BLUP_diag 

To get the conditional BLUP we have to sum BLUP_RR + BLUP_diag as follow:

```{r blup_rrdiag, warning=FALSE, message=FALSE}
blup_rr = extract_blup(mod_rrdiag1$model, pattern = "rr\\(env, [0-9]+\\)_[0-9]+\\:gen", init_row = 1 , top_n = 10)
blup_rr = blup_rr$blup

# number after the underscore
blup_rr$env  = str_extract(blup_rr$gen, "(?<=_)\\d+")

# number after the "G"
blup_rr$gen = str_extract(blup_rr$gen, "(?<=G)\\d+")

blup_rr$gen_env = paste0("G", blup_rr$gen, "_E", blup_rr$env)
blup_rr = blup_rr %>% arrange(gen_env)

# DIAG
blup_diag = extract_blup(mod_rrdiag1$model, pattern = "env_[0-9]+\\:gen", init_row = 1 , top_n = 10)

blup_diag = blup_diag$blup

# number after the underscore
blup_diag$env  = str_extract(blup_diag$gen, "(?<=env_)\\d+")

# number after the "G"
blup_diag$gen = str_extract(blup_diag$gen, "(?<=gen_G)\\d+")

blup_diag$gen_env = paste0("G", blup_diag$gen, "_E", blup_diag$env)

blup_diag = blup_diag %>% arrange(gen_env)


cblup_rr_diag = merge(blup_rr, blup_diag,
                      by = "gen_env")

cblup_rr_diag$cblup_rr_diag = cblup_rr_diag$solution.x + cblup_rr_diag$solution.y
```


## Conditional BLUPs for the rrdiag1 model.

```{r lambda1 }
# J environments x K loadings (k is the number of factors)

Lambda_hat = vc2 %>%
  bind_rows() %>%
  filter(model == "mod_rrdiag1") %>%
  # keep only rows for env:gen!env_i:j
  filter(grepl("fa[0-9]+", effect)) %>%
  select(estimate)

dim(Lambda_hat) # J x K loadings

I_V = diag(61) 
dim(I_V) # V x V identity

# scores (f_tilde)
f_tilde = extract_blup(mod_rrdiag1$model, pattern = "Comp1", init_row = 1 , top_n = 10)
f_tilde = f_tilde[["blup"]] 
f_tilde = f_tilde%>%   
  arrange(gen)

f_tilde = as.matrix(f_tilde$solution) 
dim(f_tilde) # K x V factor scores

blup_diag = extract_blup(mod_rrdiag1$model, pattern = "env_[0-9]+\\:gen", init_row = 1 , top_n = 10)
blup_diag = blup_diag$blup

blup_diag = blup_diag%>%   
  arrange(gen)

names = blup_diag$gen

blup_diag = as.matrix(blup_diag$solution) 
dim(blup_diag) # vector VJ lack of fit effects

g = (kronecker(as.matrix(Lambda_hat), as.matrix(I_V))) %*% as.vector(f_tilde) + as.vector(blup_diag)  

rownames(g) = names
dim(g)  # vector VJ

g = data.frame(g)
g$gen_env = rownames(g)

conditional_rr_diag = g 
```


